-- Balotelli Gives Italy 2-1 Confederations Cup Win Over Mexico
-- B y   T a r i q   P a n j a
-- 2013-06-16T20:52:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-16/balotelli-gives-italy-2-1-confederations-cup-win-over-mexico.html
Italy beat Mexico 2-1 in soccer’s
Confederations Cup at Rio de Janeiro’s Maracana stadium.  Andrea Pirlo , playing in his 100th game, opened the scoring
with a free kick in the 27th minute before Javier Hernandez drew
Mexico level with a penalty seven minutes later. Mario Balotelli
scored the winner in the 78th minute.  Italy joins Brazil atop Group A after the host nation beat
Japan 3-0 in the opening match of the eight-team tournament
yesterday. World champion Spain plays Uruguay tonight in the
first Group B game. Nigeria meets Tahiti tomorrow.  The Confederations Cup is a warm up event for next year’s
World Cup in Brazil. The final takes place on June 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
